BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FEET IN THE MUD- WORKSHOP 1
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260413T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260413T173000
UID:87a11300189190d58792007a77d4eed4@petalumariverpark.org
DESCRIPTION:Blood\, Sweat\, Tears &amp\; Bravery from Xinning\, Guangdong 
 to Petaluma\, California What did Chinese immigrants experience at home th
 at pushed them to come to California? In this workshop\, read selections t
 ogether as researcher Professor Chingling Wo from the Sonoma State English
  Department offers an English translation of the 19th century Chinese loca
 l gazette from Xinning (the historic name for Taishan)\, the region most o
 f the early Chinese immigrants came from. Through a short lecture\, hands-
 on activities\, and group discussion\, participants will get the chance to
  see the Chinese humanized rather than only as an empty racialized sign. L
 ocal teachers interested in teaching history of Chinese laborers in Petalu
 ma are especially encouraged to attend. Limited seating. .fe-block-c1b212d
 1036cd4236439 {mix-blend-mode: \; } Register Here #block-yui_3_17_2_1_1774
 902863513_2970 {--sqs-block-content-flex: 0\; } #block-yui_3_17_2_1_177490
