BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FEET IN THE MUD- WORKSHOP 3
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260427T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260427T173000
UID:d2aa07bee0bd0fb9e28a5b023f57be21@petalumariverpark.org
DESCRIPTION:Stages of Chinese Exclusion: Out of the Gold Mines\, Urban Fac
 tories\, and Eventually from Most Back-Breaking Farm Work We may typically
  see the Chinese Exclusion Act as a law signed by Congress in 1882\, but C
 hinese communities experienced exclusion since they arrived—in the mines
  in the 1850s\, in urban factories in the 1870s\, and in rural farm labor 
 between 1880 and 1890. Through mini-lectures\, hands-on activities\, and g
 roup discussion\, explore how these experiences ultimately shaped the Cali
 fornia agriculture system\, and why driving Chinese workers out was not a 
 victory for white laborers. Limited Seating. .fe-block-91157149afb2baf9d5a
 3 {mix-blend-mode: \; } Register Here #block-5c2a72041a61611cb533 {--sqs-b
 lock-content-flex: 0\; } #block-5c2a72041a61611cb533 { --opacity: 100%\; -
